{
  "texts": [
    "• Natural Questions (NQ) (Kwiatkowski et al., 2019) consists of real user queries from Google Search, where answers are short spans extracted from Wikipedia articles.",
    "We use 2837 questions from the development set in the KILT benchmark (Petroni et al., 2021) for evaluation.",
    "• TriviaQA (Joshi et al., 2017) includes challenging trivia questions written by trivia enthusiasts, paired with independently collected evidence documents.",
    "We use 5359 questions from the development set in the KILT benchmark (Petroni et al., 2021) for evaluation.",
    "• HotpotQA (Yang et al., 2018) is a multi-hop QA dataset that requires reasoning over multiple Wikipedia articles to answer complex questions."
  ]
}